definition: to establish/to found/to set up/to build/to construct
to hand over/to deliver/to pay (money)/to turn over/to make friends/to intersect (lines)/variant of 跤[jiao1]

sentences.english: Facts have proven that the establishment of diplomatic ties between China and Dominica conforms to the fundamental interest of both countries.
sentences.chinese: 事实证明，中多建交符合两国的根本利益。

sentences.english: This year marks the 60th anniversary of the China-Pakistan relationship.
The Chinese premier also expressed the hope that the 60th anniversary of the establishment of the Sino-Indian diplomatic ties would become a new starting point for the development of the relations.
sentences.chinese: 我希望中印建交60周年成为双边关系发展的新起点。

sentences.english: Korean-Sino relations have experienced a dramatic expansion since official diplomatic relations kicked off in 1992.
sentences.chinese: 韩中关系自1992年建交以来急剧扩张。

sentences.english: Biya said Cameroon and China have just celebrated the 40th anniversary of the establishment of diplomatic ties.
sentences.chinese: 比亚表示，喀麦隆和中国刚刚庆祝建交四十周年。

sentences.english: Over the 10 years since the establishment of diplomatic ties, the bilateral relations have been developing steadily.
sentences.chinese: 建交10年来，两国关系稳步发展。

sentences.english: Hu Jintao said that since the establishment of diplomatic ties, relations between the two countries have been developing steadily.
sentences.chinese: 胡锦涛说，中葡建交以来，两国关系稳步发展。

sentences.english: During the 8 years since the establishment of diplomatic relations between China and Belarus, the general development of bilateral relations has been at a satisfactory level.
sentences.chinese: 中白建交八年来，两国关系的总体发展水平令人满意。

sentences.english: This year celebrates the 35th anniversary of the establishment of diplomatic ties between China and Europe.
China-Luxembourg ties have progressed smoothly since the two countries established diplomatic ties 34 years ago, Hu said.
sentences.chinese: 胡锦涛说，中卢建交34年来，两国关系顺利发展。

sentences.english: Hu pointed out that this year marks the 55th anniversary of the establishment of diplomatic ties between both countries.
sentences.chinese: 胡锦涛指出，今年是中巴建交55周年。

sentences.english: Wen said that over the past 50 years since the two countries forged diplomatic relationship, China-Switzerland relations have advanced steadily.
sentences.chinese: 温家宝说，建交50多年来，中瑞关系一直稳步发展。

sentences.english: He said that Sino-Slovenian relations have advanced steadily since the two countries established diplomatic relations.
sentences.chinese: 他说，中斯建交以来，两国关系稳步发展。

sentences.english: Yet we are not afraid of any. Press Trust of India: India and China will see the 55th anniversary of their establishment of a diplomatic relationship next month.
sentences.chinese: 下个月印度和中国就要庆祝两国建交55周年了。

sentences.english: It marked the 40th anniversary of Canada-China diplomatic ties.
sentences.chinese: 它标志着加拿大与中国建交40周年了。

sentences.english: Tang Jiaxuan pointed out that relations between China and Bosnia-Herzegovina have been developing smoothly since the establishment of diplomatic relations.
sentences.chinese: 唐家璇指出，中波两国建交以来，双边关系发展平稳。
